GUI Framebuffer Overlay for a64_hook
=======================================

Portable kernel-space markdown-style GUI overlay for QEMU
virtio-gpu on Android GKI kernels (5.10-6.x). No DRM, no
fbdev — parses /proc/kallsyms at runtime for all symbols.

Features:
  - Markdown-style rendering in kernel space
  - Rectangles, text, colors (hex RGB like FF0F3460)
  - Virtual window management with Z-ordering
  - FPS counter and swap chain
  - Procfs control interface: /proc/a64_hook_gui
  - virtio-gpu framebuffer backend (virtio-gpu-pci)

Control commands (echo to /proc/a64_hook_gui):
  clear FF1A1A2E              — clear to color
  rect x y w h color          — filled rectangle
  text x y fg bg "string"     — render text
  fps                         — toggle FPS counter
  window id x y w h           — create/resize window
  swap                        — swap buffers (double-buffer)

QEMU test:
  cd qemu_test/
  ./run.sh gui                — VNC mode (localhost:5900)
  Connect via: open vnc://localhost:5900

Dependencies:
  - CONFIG_VIRTIO_GPU=y (or =m) in kernel
  - QEMU -device virtio-gpu-pci
  - /proc/kallsyms readable

Files:
  src/a64_hook_gui.c       — GUI rendering engine
  src/a64_hook_gui_win.c   — window manager
  src/a64_hook_virtio_fb.c — virtio-gpu fb backend

